ay be incomplete or unstable. Currently only tested on macOS. See Known Issues below before using in production."},"11":{"id":"/docs-9","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"React Native Native lets you write native components and modules in **any compiled language** — Rust, C++, Kotlin/Compose, Swift/ObjC — and hot-reload them on a physical device, just like JavaScript."},"12":{"id":"/docs-10","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#why","content":"React Native's native module system requires you to write Swift/Kotlin wrappers, maintain Xcode/Android Studio projects, and rebuild the entire app for every change. React Native Native removes all of that:"},"13":{"id":"/docs-11","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#why","content":"**Write native code in your editor** — no IDE switching"},"14":{"id":"/docs-12","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#why","content":"**Save and see** — Metro compiles, signs, and hot-reloads native code on device"},"15":{"id":"/docs-13","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#why","content":"**Full platform SDK access** — use any iOS framework or Android API directly"},"16":{"id":"/docs-14","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#why","content":"**Works with Expo** — drops into any Expo project as a module"},"17":{"id":"/docs-15","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#how-it-works","content":"Your native code becomes a React component or module that JS can use like any other:"},"18":{"id":"/docs-16","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#development","content":"Metro watches your native files alongside JavaScript. When you save a `.cpp`, `.rs`, `.swift`, or `.kt` file:"},"19":{"id":"/docs-17","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#development","content":"**Metro compiles** it to a signed dynamic library (`.dylib` on iOS, `.dex` on Android)"},"20":{"id":"/docs-18","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#development","content":"**Device pulls** the compiled library over HTTP — same as a JS bundle refresh"},"21":{"id":"/docs-19","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#development","content":"**Runtime loads** it via `dlopen` (iOS) or `DexClassLoader` (Android)"},"22":{"id":"/docs-20","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#development","content":"**Hot-reload** — your changes appear on device in seconds, no full rebuild"},"23":{"id":"/docs-21","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#development","content":"This works on both simulators and physical devices. Metro auto-detects the target architecture and compiles accordingly."},"24":{"id":"/docs-22","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#production","content":"In release builds, all native code is statically linked into the app binary. No dynamic libraries, no runtime code loading."},"25":{"id":"/docs-23","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#production","content":"**iOS** — A CocoaPods script phase runs before compilation:"},"26":{"id":"/docs-24","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#production","content":"Scans your project for native files (`.cpp`, `.mm`, `.swift`, `.rs`)"},"27":{"id":"/docs-25","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#production","content":"Generates combined bridge files — one `.mm` for all C++/ObjC++ bridges, one `.swift` for all Swift bridges"},"28":{"id":"/docs-26","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#production","content":"Compiles Rust into a single static library (`libnativ_user.a`)"},"29":{"id":"/docs-27","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#production","content":"Xcode compiles and links everything into the app binary"},"30":{"id":"/docs-28","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#production","content":"**Android** — A Gradle pre-build task does the same:"},"31":{"id":"/docs-29","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#production","content":"Generates per-module bridge files and Kotlin wrappers"},"32":{"id":"/docs-30","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#production","content":"Compiles Rust for all ABIs (arm64, armv7, x86\\_64, x86)"},"33":{"id":"/docs-31","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#production","content":"Gradle compiles and packages everything into the APK"},"34":{"id":"/docs-32","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#production","content":"Metro only bundles JavaScript in production — all native code is handled by the platform build system."},"35":{"id":"/docs-33","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#production","content":"See Production Builds for details on EAS Build and CI setup."},"36":{"id":"/docs-34","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#known-issues","content":"**Zig support** — planned but not yet available."},"37":{"id":"/docs-35","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#language-setup","content":"C++, Objective-C++, and Swift work out of the box with no additional setup. Some languages have additional setup steps for your development environment — see the individual language guides for details:"},"38":{"id":"/docs-36","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#language-setup","content":"Rust — install Rust targets and create `Cargo.toml`"},"39":{"id":"/docs-37","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#language-setup","content":"Kotlin — download the Kotlin compiler toolchain"},"40":{"id":"/docs-38","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#language-setup","content":"Kotlin with Compose — additional Compose compiler toolchain"},"41":{"id":"/docs-39","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#next-steps","content":"<Card title=\"Installation\" href=\"/docs/getting-started/installation\" />"},"42":{"id":"/docs-40","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#next-steps",